== F.6 — The Primary Competency Evidence: Plant Stone Diagnostic

The physical diagnostic test for the Procedurally Complete Plant Stone is applied before Year Two is confirmed:

#lab[
  *Wax-Flow Test*
  + Warm the cohobated preparation gently in a water bath to approximately 37°C.
  + Observe its consistency.
  + *Pass:* The preparation softens and exhibits a plastic, wax-like quality — it flows slowly when tilted and yields to gentle pressure.
  + *Fail:* The preparation remains dry, brittle, and inert regardless of warmth.

  A failing preparation indicates that the natural moisture has been destroyed through overheating during calcination or cohobation. Review the Four Common Errors (Appendix D.3). The student must begin again with a fresh portion of herb if this diagnostic fails.
]